```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "rnnvae",
    "partition": "high",
    "workdir": "/homedtic/gmarti/CODE/RNN-VAE",
    "memory": "16G",
    "gpu": "1",
    "stdout": "LOGS/vae1_%J.out",
    "stderr": "LOGS/vae1_%j.err",
    "modules": [
      "Python",
      "CUDA/10.2.89",
      "cuDNN/7.6.5.32-CUDA-10.2.89"
    ],
    "environment": "/homedtic/gmarti/pytorch/bin/activate",
    "script": "scripts_mc/metaexp_synth_pad.py"
  }
}
```

This script is running on SLURM, a workload manager for high-performance computing systems. It defines a job named "rnnvae" that runs on the "high" partition, uses 16 GB of memory, one GPU, and writes output to specific log files. The script also loads various modules, including Python, CUDA, and cuDNN, and activates a virtual environment located at `/homedtic/gmarti/pytorch/bin`. Finally, it runs a Python script named `metaexp_synth_pad.py`.
